Suppose there are two players, A and B, who are playing a zero-sum game. Player A can choose between strategies x and y, while player B can choose between strategies z and w. The payoff matrix is shown below:

\begin{array}{c|cc} & z & w \\ \hline x & 2 & -1 \\ y & -3 & 4 \end{array}

Find the optimal strategy for each player, i.e., the strategy that maximizes their minimum possible payoff, and the value of the game.
